Machine Learning Syllabus

1. Introduction to Machine Learning

* Definition and Scope of ML
* Types of Machine Learning: Supervised, Unsupervised, Reinforcement
* Applications of ML
* Difference between AI, ML, and DL

2. Mathematical Foundations

* Linear Algebra: Vectors, Matrices, Eigenvalues, Eigenvectors, Matrix operations
* Probability and Statistics: Distributions, Conditional probability, Bayes theorem, Expectation, Variance, Hypothesis testing
* Calculus and Optimization: Differentiation, Gradient, Partial Derivatives, Gradient Descent, Convex Optimization

3. Supervised Learning

* Regression: Linear, Multiple, Polynomial, Logistic Regression
* Classification: Decision Trees, Na√Øve Bayes, k-NN, SVM, Perceptron
* Ensemble Methods: Bagging, Random Forest, Boosting (AdaBoost, Gradient Boosting, XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost)
* Evaluation Metrics: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1 Score, ROC, AUC

4. Unsupervised Learning

* Clustering: k-Means, Hierarchical, DBSCAN
* Dimensionality Reduction: PCA, LDA, t-SNE, UMAP
* Association Rule Learning: Apriori, FP-Growth

5. Reinforcement Learning

* Basics of RL
* Markov Decision Processes
* Value Iteration, Policy Iteration
* Q-Learning, SARSA
* Deep Q-Networks

6. Model Selection and Evaluation

* Train/Test Split, Cross Validation
* Bias-Variance Tradeoff
* Underfitting vs Overfitting
* Regularization: L1, L2, Elastic Net
* Hyperparameter Tuning: Grid Search, Random Search, Bayesian Optimization

7. Feature Engineering

* Feature Selection: Filter, Wrapper, Embedded Methods
* Feature Scaling: Normalization, Standardization
* Encoding: One-hot, Label Encoding, Target Encoding
* Handling Missing Data: Imputation methods
* Outlier Detection and Treatment

8. Neural Networks and Deep Learning (Introduction)

* Basics of Neural Networks
* Activation Functions: Sigmoid, ReLU, Tanh, Softmax
* Backpropagation Algorithm
* Introduction to TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras

9. Advanced Machine Learning Topics

* Semi-Supervised Learning
* Online and Incremental Learning
* Transfer Learning
* Graph-Based Learning
* Bayesian Machine Learning

10. Practical Machine Learning

* End-to-End ML Pipeline: Data Preprocessing, Model Training, Deployment
* Handling Imbalanced Data: Oversampling, Undersampling, SMOTE
* MLOps Basics
* Tools and Libraries: NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn

11. Applications of Machine Learning

* Healthcare, Finance, Retail, Social Media, Industry 4.0

12. Research and Case Studies

* Benchmark Datasets (MNIST, CIFAR, IMDB, UCI)
* Real-world ML model implementation
* ML Research Papers
* Current Trends: AutoML, Explainable ML, Fairness in ML

